OL,3,CUK's first Reform council leader
OL,4,Cpromises Leicestershire tax cuts
OL,6,FThe party has opted to govern as a
OL,7,Fminority administration rather than
OL,8,Ftrying to form a coalition with
OL,9,Fanother party.
OL,11,FMeanwhile, Reform UK in Derbyshire has
OL,12,Fannounced Alan Graves, the former
OL,13,FMayor of Derby, as its new leader
OL,14,Fafter the party unseated the
OL,15,FConservatives across the East Midlands.
OL,17,FAlthough already selected as the
OL,18,Fleader of Derbyshire's largest party,
OL,19,Fhe can only be confirmed as leader of
OL,20,Fthe council at a full council meeting
OL,21,Fon 21 May.
